The paper focuses on the problem of entity alignment in Knowledge Graphs (KG) using Graph Convolutional Networks (GCN), which is a popular technique in the fields of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses evaluation approaches and benchmark datasets, which are relevant to the fields of databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), and natural language processing (cs.CL).
